DESCRIPTION:** FOR THIS ASSIGNMENT YOU MUST UPLOAD YOUR VIDEO AND YOUR SCRI
 PT **\n\nFor this project you will need to:\n\n#1. Get with your partner o
 r team. Remember partners/teams can be found in [People ] (https://canvas.
 unl.edu/courses/212549/users)- under the "Project Groups" tab.  You DO NO
 T have to use a partner from your Project Group\, this is an individual as
 signment.\n\n#2. Read the case - [Kings Hawaiian Sales Case -1.pdf] (https
 ://canvas.unl.edu/courses/212549/files/23552714?wrap=1)[] (https://canvas.
 unl.edu/courses/47734/files/2464189/download?wrap=1)\n\n#3. Write a script
  in which the Seller (you) has a meeting with Jan Sawyer (your customer).\
 n\n* The meeting should EXACTLY follow the project rubric\, and include es
 tablishing rapport and asking a series of questions to learn more about Ja
 n's issues and the issues that Best Foods is facing. \n\n* Please know th
 at if you miss sections of the rubric you will lose those points\n\n* Use 
 the SPIN project rubric as the outline for drafting your script: \n\n[ima
 ge.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/212549/files/23552697/preview)\n\n
 * Scroll down the page to the rubric to see expectations for each of the f
 our sections. \n\n* **if you want help building out your role play script
 \, you can use this script builder worksheet. It will help your break the 
 script into parts and hopefully make it a little less overwhelming to put 
 together:[M257 CM _ worksheet for building out role play script.docx] (htt
 ps://canvas.unl.edu/courses/212549/files/23552731?wrap=1)[Download M257 RG
  _ worksheet for building out role play script.docx] (https://canvas.unl.e
 du/courses/170098/files/17664180/download?download_frd=1)\n\n* If you nee
 d more information on SPIN selling\, you can review Chapter 8 in the textb
 ook prior to us covering it in class.\n\n#5. Reserve a time/day for a ro
 le-play room on our class's assigned days (Begin reserving rooms in the l
 ab on March 2nd). The Sales Lab will be open for recording on March 4th a
 nd March 5th from 8:30 am to 4:00 pm. These are the only two days when yo
 u can record your role plays.  \n\n#6. Purchase or borrow a jump/USB dr
 ive (32G max size)- you need it to save your role-play video from the sale
 s lab. SHARING A USB OFTEN CREATES ISSUES FOR STUDENTS\, I WOULD RECOMMEN
 D EACH STUDENT HAVING THEIR OWN USB FOR THEIR OWN VIDEO.\n\n#7. Record yo
 ur role play in the Sales Lab. Each student must submit a recording of the
 mselves as the Seller.\n\n* You will not be graded when you are doing the 
 role-play as the Buyer\, only as the Seller.\n\n* You may not have your sc
 ript with you during your role-play\, but you may have an index card with 
 notes on both sides to help you remember how you want the meeting to go.\n
 \n* Instructions on how to use the sales lab recording equipment can be fo
 und in the lab.\n\n#8. Once your recording is done\, upload your video an
 d your script to this Canvas assignment. Upload the video in which you ar
 e the Seller.\n\n* Uploading your script helps us grade your role play mor
 e effectively as we can see what you have written - you will likely earn a
  better grade if you upload your script and we can see what you are trying
  to accomplish in your role play\n\nIf you have questions\, please reach o
 ut to your professor or TA
