DESCRIPTION:[BSAD222 Banner - June 2017-1-1.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/co
 urses/208826/files/23678774/preview)\n\n \n\nOn Friday\, May 1st\, all st
 udents will participate in our BSAD 222 Professional Networking Event\, wh
 ich serves as the capstone experience for this course.\n\nThis event is de
 signed to give you the opportunity to confidently connect with employers i
 n a structured and supportive environment. You will practice introducing y
 ourself professionally\, sharing your interests\, strengths\, skills\, and
  values\, and engaging in meaningful conversations while building real-wor
 ld connections. Think of this as your opportunity to apply what you’ve l
 earned this semester in a professional setting created specifically for yo
 u.\n\nParticipation in this event is required to successfully complete BSA
 D 222.\n\nFor this assignment\, please submit a screenshot of your slot re
 gistration (Sample Below)\n\nRegistering for Your Slot:\n\nAll students sh
 ould have received an email in their Huskers Email from Kadina Koonce via 
 Quickbase with instructions to register for a networking time slot (regist
 ration invitation was sent Monday\, March 9th\, around 10:00 am). Reach ou
 t to Dayton Heffelfinger via Canvas for support. \n\nYou may select:\n\n*
  Your assigned class time\, or\n\n* Another available time slot that works
  with your schedule\n\nEach timeframe is capped at 260 students (some list
  multiple locations). Once a slot reaches capacity\, you will need to sele
 ct another available option. Registering early will increase your chances 
 of securing your preferred time. \n\n* Before saving\, the Timeslot – D
 ate and Time field will appear white. Once a time is selected and saved\, 
 it will turn grey to indicate confirmation.\n\n* If your assigned class ti
 me fills\, you must choose a different available time and check availabili
 ty at a future date. The ability to swap times will be available through A
 pril 10th. Add your confirmed time to your calendar as soon as possible. 
 \n\n* If you have a class conflict that prevents you from attending anothe
 r time\, select the option indicating your preference for your assigned cl
 ass time and email your instructor via Canvas a screenshot confirming your
  conflict to discuss options.\n\nIf you cannot find your confirmation emai
 l\, please check your spam/junk folder before reaching out to Dayton Heffe
 lfinger via Canvas Inbox for support. If there is an inconsistency with yo
 ur registration\, you may be asked to resubmit this assignment. \n\nAtten
 dance Expectations: \n\nOnce registered\, please save your selected date 
 and time in your calendar. Because this event serves as the course capston
 e\, attendance is essential. Students who do not attend their scheduled ne
 tworking session will not pass the course.\n\nWork schedules and athletic 
 practices are not considered valid conflicts for this academic requirement
 \, as arrangements can be made in advance with supervisors or coaches.\n\n
 If you have an extenuating circumstance\, you must communicate with your p
 rimary instructor within the first week of class. Exceptions will be revie
 wed on a case-by-case basis.\n\nAssignment Submission Sample:\n\n[222 Netw
 orking Registration Screenshot.JPG] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826
 /files/24188070/preview)\n\n \n\nFAQ:\n\n* What if I didn't get an email?
  - Please check your spam\, clutter\, and junk folders for "Quickbase". If
  you don't have anything within 24 hours of the initial email\, please use
  Canvas inbox to contact Dayton Heffelfinger (Canvas Inbox attaches your s
 ection number to the message by default).\n\n* What if I get an error page
 ? - If you get an error page noting "This report isn't available at this t
 ime" leave the link and select it again. This error is typically caused by
  pressing the home button\, trying to sign in\, or pressing the back butto
 n. Your link is directly tied to you and should just show the time selecti
 on.\n\n* How do I know if I've completed it properly? - If you save and al
 l boxes are grey (showing a selected date\, time\, and location)\, you're 
 good to go! \n\n* Will I receive a confirmation email? - No. Your link an
 d screenshot of all registration boxes being grey is your confirmation. Yo
 u will be sent reminders during the first week of April\, the Monday of ne
 tworking week\, and the day before. Please add your selected time to your 
 calendar.\n\n* What if my name is listed incorrectly? - Email your instruc
 tor and Dayton Heffelfinger via Canvas inbox. Canvas is preferred over ema
 il because your section is attached\, which allows us to provide support m
 ore quickly. 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:End-of-semester (May 1st) Networking Capstone Confirmation [BSAD-22
