 n<p data-start="503" data-end="825">This event is designed to give you the
  opportunity to confidently connect with employers in a structured and sup
 portive environment. You will practice introducing yourself professionally
 \, sharing your interests\, strengths\, skills\, and values\, and engaging
  in meaningful conversations while building real-world connections. Think 
 of this as your opportunity to apply what you’ve learned this semester i
 n a professional setting created specifically for you.</p>\n<p data-start=
 "961" data-end="1049">Participation in this event is required to successfu
 lly complete BSAD 222.</p>\n<p data-start="961" data-end="1049"><span styl
 e="background-color: #fbeeb8\;"><strong>For this assignment\, please submi
 t a screenshot of your slot registration (Sample Below)</strong></span></p
 >\n<hr>\n<p data-start="1085" data-end="1206"><strong>Registering for Your
  Slot:</strong></p>\n<p data-start="1085" data-end="1206">All students sho
 uld have received an email in their Huskers Email from Kadina Koonce via Q
 uickbase with instructions to register for a networking time slot <span st
 yle="background-color: #fbeeb8\;">(registration invitation was sent Monday
 \, March 9th\, around 10:00 am)</span>. Reach out to Dayton Heffelfinger v
 ia Canvas for support.&nbsp\;</p>\n<p data-start="1208" data-end="1223">Yo
 u may select:</p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start="1226" data-end="1256">Your assign
 ed class time\, or</li>\n<li data-start="1259" data-end="1318">Another ava
 ilable time slot that works with your schedule</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=
 "1320" data-end="1519">Each timeframe is capped at 260 students (some list
  multiple locations). Once a slot reaches capacity\, you will need to sele
 ct another available option. Registering early will increase your chances 
 of securing your preferred time.&nbsp\;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="backgr
 ound-color: #fbeeb8\;">Before saving\, the Timeslot – Date and Time fiel
 d will appear white. <strong>Once a time is selected and saved\, it will t
 urn grey to indicate confirmation.</strong></span></li>\n<li data-start="1
 521" data-end="1599">If your assigned class time fills\, you must choose a
  different available time and check availability at a future date. The abi
 lity to swap times will be available through <span style="background-color
 : #fbeeb8\;"><strong>April 10th. Add your confirmed time to your calendar 
 as soon as possible.&nbsp\;</strong></span>\n</li>\n<li data-start="1521" 
 data-end="1599">If you have a class conflict that prevents you from attend
 ing another time\, select the option indicating your preference for your a
 ssigned class time and email your instructor via Canvas a screenshot confi
 rming your conflict to discuss options.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>If you cannot 
 find your confirmation email\, please check your spam/junk folder before r
 eaching out to Dayton Heffelfinger <span style="text-decoration: underline
 \;">via Canvas Inbox</span> for support. If there is an inconsistency with
  your registration\, you may be asked to resubmit this assignment.&nbsp\;<
 /em></p>\n<hr>\n<p data-start="2031" data-end="2105"><strong>Attendance Ex
 pectations:&nbsp\;</strong></p>\n<p data-start="2031" data-end="2105">Once
  registered\, please save your selected date and time in your calendar. Be
 cause this event serves as the course capstone\, attendance is essential. 
 Students who do not attend their scheduled networking session will not pas
 s the course.</p>\n<p data-start="2031" data-end="2105">Work schedules and
  athletic practices are not considered valid conflicts for this academic r
 equirement\, as arrangements can be made in advance with supervisors or co
 aches.</p>\n<p data-start="2271" data-end="2446">If you have an extenuatin
 g circumstance\, you must communicate with your primary instructor within 
 the first week of class. Exceptions will be reviewed on a case-by-case bas
 is.</p>\n<hr data-start="2448" data-end="2451">\n<p><strong>Assignment Sub
 mission Sample:</strong></p>\n<p><img id="24175678" src="https://canvas.un
 l.edu/courses/208826/files/24188070/preview" alt="222 Networking Registrat
 ion Screenshot.JPG" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/cours
 es/208826/files/24188070" data-api-returntype="File" loading="lazy"></p>\n
 <p>&nbsp\;</p>\n<p><strong>FAQ:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<span style="tex
 t-decoration: underline\;"><strong>What if I didn't get an email? - </stro
 ng></span>Please check your spam\, clutter\, and junk folders for "Quickba
 se". If you don't have anything within 24 hours of the initial email\, ple
 ase use Canvas inbox to contact<strong> Dayton Heffelfinger</strong> (Canv
 as Inbox attaches your section number to the message by default).</li>\n<l
 i>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline\;"><strong>What if I get an er
 ror page? </strong></span>- If you get an error page noting "This report i
 sn't available at this time" leave the link and select it again. This erro
 r is typically caused by pressing the home button\, trying to sign in\, or
  pressing the back button. Your link is directly tied to you and should ju
 st show the time selection.</li>\n<li>\n<span style="text-decoration: unde
 rline\;"><strong>How do I know if I've completed it properly? </strong></s
 pan>- If you save and all boxes are grey (showing a selected date\, time\,
  and location)\, you're good to go!&nbsp\;</li>\n<li>\n<span style="text-d
 ecoration: underline\;"><strong>Will I receive a confirmation email?</stro
 ng></span> - No. Your link and screenshot of all registration boxes being 
 grey is your confirmation. You will be sent reminders during the first wee
 k of April\, the Monday of networking week\, and the day before. Please ad
 d your selected time to your calendar.</li>\n<li>\n<span style="text-decor
 ation: underline\;"><strong>What if my name is listed incorrectly?</strong
 ></span> - Email your instructor and <strong>Dayton Heffelfinger</strong> 
 via Canvas inbox. Canvas is preferred over email because your section is a
 ttached\, which allows us to provide support more quickly.&nbsp\;</li>\n</
 ul><script src="https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_65070
 000000000001/attachments/21770614/dp_app.js"></script>
END:VEVENT
