DESCRIPTION:[BSAD222 Banner - June 2017-1-1.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/co
 urses/208826/files/23678774/preview)\n\nIn Module 1\, we explore how résu
 més communicate your professional story and how to intentionally design t
 hem to highlight strengths\, skills\, and experiences that align with your
  goals. While everyone seems to have advice about what a “good résumé
 ” looks like\, the key is understanding why certain strategies work and 
 how to create a résumé that represents you authentically and effectively
 . In this assignment to kick off our foundation to resumes\, we will exami
 ne several common résumé myths and discuss how to build strong\, tailore
 d documents that evolve as career goals and opportunities shift.\n\nRead: 
 [Week 1 Slides] (https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/UNL-BusinessCare
 erCenter/IQCjM1pOtNsLTZCc5qgur55fAVpKQBL6hXPNRyD5dTd04vc?e=96HfdD)\n\n* Sl
 ides 1-6 are introductory content and highlights from the syllabus\n\n* Sl
 ides7-10 focus on resume myths and reframes \n\n* Slides 11-17 focus on C
 oB resume expectations for structuring and strategizing your resume\n\n* S
 lide 18 shows how to get creative \n\nAfter reviewing the slides from thi
 s week\, this quiz asks that you reply to the following prompts:\n\n1. Whi
 ch of the statement(s) below did you initially find the most convincing\, 
 why? \n\n    “I don’t have enough experience to make a résumé.”
  \n\n    “One résumé can work for all applications.” \n\n    
 “Résumés should be creative or flashy to stand out.” \n\n    “A
  résumé is just a list of jobs and tasks.” \n\n2. Find one article or
  piece of data that disproves one of the statements above and provide the 
 link. What explanation was given about the topic\, and how did this inform
 ation influence or shift your thinking? \n\n3. Which 2–3 CliftonStrengt
 hs (or skills) do you want an employer to notice when they read your résu
 mé\, and why?\n\n4. Which résumé sections were new to you after reading
  the slides? Which sections would you add to your current document\, or co
 nsider adding later\, and why?\n\n5. After reviewing the slides\, what con
 cept\, slide\, or recommendation about résumé structure or strategy stoo
 d out to you most\, and why?\n\nGrading:\nThis is a complete/incomplete as
 signment. You will receive a “Complete” if you fully address all prom
 pts and components of each question in your own voice\, with sufficient de
 tail to demonstrate your understanding of the content.\n\nNote: If you sco
 re an "Incomplete"\, you are required to review your moderator's feedback 
 and resubmit within the timeline provided.
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Module 1: Assess Your Defining Experiences (Virtual) [BSAD-222-951.
 1261]
