 6&month=03&year=2026#assignment_2273016
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://instructu
 re-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_65070000000000001/attachments/21770615
 /dp_app.css"><p><img id="23668674" src="https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208
 826/files/23678774/preview" alt="BSAD222 Banner - June 2017-1-1.png" loadi
 ng="lazy" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/courses/208826/
 files/23678774" data-api-returntype="File"></p>\n<p>In Module 1\, we explo
 re how résumés communicate your professional story and how to intentiona
 lly design them to highlight strengths\, skills\, and experiences that ali
 gn with your goals. While everyone seems to have advice about what a “go
 od résumé” looks like\, the key is understanding why certain strategie
 s work and how to create a résumé that represents you authentically and 
 effectively. In this assignment to kick off our foundation to resumes\, we
  will examine several common résumé myths and discuss how to build stron
 g\, tailored documents that evolve as career goals and opportunities shift
 .</p>\n<p><strong><span data-contrast="auto">Read:</span></strong> <a clas
 s="inline_disabled" href="https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/UNL-Bus
 inessCareerCenter/IQCjM1pOtNsLTZCc5qgur55fAVpKQBL6hXPNRyD5dTd04vc?e=96HfdD
 " target="_blank"><span>Week 1 Slides</span></a><em><br></em></p>\n<ul>\n<
 li><span data-ccp-props="{&quot\;134233117&quot\;:false\,&quot\;134233118&
 quot\;:false\,&quot\;335559738&quot\;:240\,&quot\;335559739&quot\;:240}">S
 lides 1-6 are introductory content and highlights from the syllabus</span>
 </li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props="{&quot\;134233117&quot\;:false\,&quot\;13
 4233118&quot\;:false\,&quot\;335559738&quot\;:240\,&quot\;335559739&quot\;
 :240}">Slides7-10 focus on resume myths and reframes&nbsp\;</span></li>\n<
 li><span data-ccp-props="{&quot\;134233117&quot\;:false\,&quot\;134233118&
 quot\;:false\,&quot\;335559738&quot\;:240\,&quot\;335559739&quot\;:240}">S
 lides 11-17 focus on CoB resume expectations for structuring and strategiz
 ing your resume</span></li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props="{&quot\;134233117&q
 uot\;:false\,&quot\;134233118&quot\;:false\,&quot\;335559738&quot\;:240\,&
 quot\;335559739&quot\;:240}">Slide 18 shows how to get creative&nbsp\;</sp
 an></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>After reviewing the slides from this week\, this
  quiz asks that you reply to the following prompts:</p>\n<p>1. Which of th
 e statement(s) below did you initially find the most convincing\, why?&nbs
 p\;</p>\n<p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; “I don’t have enough experience to make a 
 résumé.”&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; “One résumé can work for a
 ll applications.”&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; “Résumés should be 
 creative or flashy to stand out.”&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; “A r
 ésumé is just a list of jobs and tasks.”&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>2. Find one ar
 ticle or piece of data that disproves one of the statements above and prov
 ide the link. What explanation was given about the topic\, and how did thi
 s information influence or shift your thinking?&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>3. Which 2
 –3 CliftonStrengths (or skills) do you want an employer to notice when t
 hey read your résumé\, and why?</p>\n<p>4. Which résumé sections were 
 new to you after reading the slides? Which sections would you add to your 
 current document\, or consider adding later\, and why?</p>\n<p>5. After re
 viewing the slides\, what concept\, slide\, or recommendation about résum
 é structure or strategy stood out to you most\, and why?</p>\n<hr>\n<p><s
 pan><strong>Grading:<br>This is a complete/incomplete assignment.&nbsp\;</
 strong>You will receive a “Complete” if you fully address all prompts 
 and components of each question in your own voice\, with sufficient detail
  to demonstrate your understanding of the content.</span></p>\n<p><span st
 yle="background-color: #fbeeb8\;">Note: If you score an "Incomplete"\, you
  are required to review your moderator's feedback and resubmit within the 
 timeline provided.</span></p><script src="https://instructure-uploads.s3.a
 mazonaws.com/account_65070000000000001/attachments/21770614/dp_app.js"></s
 cript>
