DESCRIPTION:-------------------------\nBig Interview Résumé Scan\n-------
 ------------------\n\n Overview\n---------\n\nNow that you've finished cr
 eating/updating your document\, we will next focus on fine-tuning the basi
 cs. With the widespread use of Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS)\, many res
 umes are first screened by artificial intelligence before ever reaching a 
 human recruiter. To be a competitive applicant for positions\, it is impor
 tant that the formatting of your résumé be simple\, consistent\, and eas
 y to read. This assignment is designed to\n\n* Introduce you to the realit
 ies of modern resume screening and empower you to optimize your document f
 or both AI and human review.\n\n* Provide feedback from a simulated applic
 ant tracking system on areas of your formatting that still need improvemen
 t\n\n* Ensure your résumé formatting looks professional and is ready for
  your 1:1 coaching session\n\nSubmission Requirements: \n\n* Upload your 
 newly edited résumé into Big Interview's Resume Scan.\n\n*\n\n* You are 
 REQUIRED to utilize one of the College of Business résumé formats.\n\n* 
 See the [Building Your Resume Instructions] (https://canvas.unl.edu/course
 s/208826/pages/building-your-resume-instructions-2) page to be sure you ha
 ve a strong start before uploading\, as you only have 5 scan opportunities
  available to you per day.\n\n* Receive a "Gold" rating from Big Interview
  before signing up for your [Resume Coaching Session.] (https://canvas.unl
 .edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251640)\n\n* If you did not receive a "Go
 ld" rating\, view the feedback provided to edit your document or reach out
  to a coach for support.\n\n  STOP!\n\nHave you edited your résumé usi
 ng one of the approved College of Business résumé formats?\nYou only hav
 e 5 scans available to you per day\, so editing your resume to course stan
 dards is paramount before uploading your first document to Big Interview.\
 n\n Resources\n----------\n\nThis assignment aligns with the [Building Yo
 ur Resume Instructions] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/build
 ing-your-resume-instructions-2) and prepares you for your [Revised Résum
 é] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251666) and [1:1 R
 ésumé Coaching Session] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignmen
 ts/2251638). If you have not reviewed the Building Your Resume content\, 
 go back before you begin.\n\n Instructions\n-------------\n\n1. Create Yo
 ur Account & Access the Scoring Guide\n-----------------------------------
 --------------\n\nCreate an account in [Big Interview] (https://unl.bigint
 erview.com/) using your @huskers.unl.edu email address.\n\n* Utilize 4024 
 when prompted for the access code.\n\nOnce you've created your account an
 d completed building your resume with a College of Business-approved forma
 t:\n\n* Find the College of Business Resume Scoring Guide with a Join Code
  by selecting "Scan" at the top of the screen\, then "ResumeAI".\n\n* Ente
 r Code f20092 in the "Join by code" box and select "Join"\n\n[Screenshot o
 f Big interview showing the home page with "Scan" selected then "ResumeAI"
  highlighted by a red box.] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/2
 3677584/preview)[Screenshot of Big interview showing the "Scan Resume" pag
 e then a red box around the "Join Code" job on the right with code f20092 
 entered.] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678528/preview)\n
 \n2. Upload & Scan Resume\n-----------------------\n\nThe first page will 
 have an option to upload a job description in addition to your resume docu
 ment. DO NOT upload a job description. Your scan will work without one and
  focus solely on formatting and content.\n\n[Screenshot of Big interview s
 howing the "Scan Resume" page crossing out the "Add job description" secti
 on ] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677588/preview)\n  \
 n\nChoose your Revised Resume file in the College of Business approved for
 mat. Make sure it is saved as a .pdf or .docx before uploading. Keep in mi
 nd\, you are limited to 5 scans per day. The system does take a bit to sca
 n\, so expect the scan to take 3-5 minutes. You should get an email upon s
 can completion as well.\n\n[Screenshot of Big interview showing "Step 2" t
 he upload resume section. This page also shows an option to "Choose File" 
 that is in PDF or docx format for a max of 5.0mb. In the bottom left it al
 so shows the number of scan provided in a day which is 5 and an "Exit" and
  "Scan Resume" button on the right side by side ] (https://canvas.unl.edu/
 courses/208826/files/23678724/preview)\n\n3. View Score and Feedback\n----
 ----------------------\n\nYour completed scans will be located on your das
 hboard\, noting the date of the scan and the score you received. For this 
 assignment\, you need to receive a Gold score before signing up for your R
 esume Coaching Session. From your dashboard\, click VIEW FEEDBACK.\n\n[Scr
 eenshot of Big Interview scan history showing the title of the the Scoring
  guide then a list of scores (gold\, silver\, bronze) alongside upload dat
 es and options to "view feedback" for each upload ] (https://canvas.unl.ed
 u/courses/208826/files/23678864/preview)     \n\n4. Submit Your Screens
 hot\n-------------------------\n\nThe screenshot below is an approved imag
 e to upload for completion of this assignment. To get to this page\, you n
 eed to click on VIEW DETAILED FEEDBACK on the feedback page. Your submissi
 on needs to visibly show your Gold rating and the body of your scanned res
 ume with your name.\n\n[Screenshot of the "view feedback" page of big inte
 rview. It shows a "Gold" rating at the top left with gold for all sections
  (readability\, credibility\, and format). It lists action items on the le
 ft and shows feedback form the CoB coach as well as AI generated feedback.
  To the Right is a student resume sample.] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses
 /208826/files/23677344/preview)\n   \n\n Grading and Feedback\n-------
 --------------\n\nThis assignment will be graded as Complete or Incomplete
 . A screenshot of your Gold rating that also shows your resume with your n
 ame is all that is needed. A resume with a score lower than Gold will need
  to be edited based on the detailed feedback provided and re-scanned until
  a Gold rating is received. \n\nDO NOT schedule your 1:1 Resume Coaching 
 Session until you have received a Gold rating on your scanned Revised Resu
 me.\n\n FAQs\n-----\n\nWhat if I'm having trouble accessing my account?\n
 Be sure you have created your account using your @huskers.unl.edu email ad
 dress and the provided access code in step 1 of the instructions above. If
  you continue to have trouble\, please reach out to the primary instructor
  as soon as possible for assistance.\n\nWhat do I do if I run out of scans
 ?\nIf an extension is not needed\, please review the feedback provided clo
 sely to edit your document and wait to scan the next day. If you feel you 
 have made the appropriate edits but are not receiving the necessary score\
 , please send your moderator a screenshot and ask for support. You're also
  welcome to call or visit our office for drop-in availability.\n\nWhat if 
 I want to use a job description with my resume scan?\nYou're welcome to do
  so\, but it may significantly impact your score or ability to get the sco
 re required for this assignment. After achieving a "Gold" rating without a
  job description\, you're more than welcome to use the job description fea
 ture to optimize your current or future resumes.\n\nMy resume was uploaded
  10 minutes ago and is taking forever to scan. What can I do? \nThe most 
 common issue is likely that you have exported your document from Google Do
 cs or are using an older version of Microsoft Word. Please ensure your res
 ume is saved as a DOCX or PDF file format. If you are using the correct fi
 le type\, below are some additional troubleshooting suggestions:\n\n* Veri
 fy that a Scoring Guide is selected before scanning\; otherwise\, the scan
  won’t run.\n\n* Upload a text-based PDF (not an image-only PDF). \n\n*
  Use Chrome or Edge\; try an incognito window\; close extra Big Interview 
 tabs\; refresh ResumeAI and re-upload if “Scanning…” lasts >3–5 mi
 nutes.\n\n* Avoid VPNs or aggressive ad/script blockers\; temporarily disa
 ble extensions and try a different network if possible.\n\n* If you contin
 ue to have trouble\, reach out to BigInterview Support directly using the 
 chatbot or via email at [support@biginterview.com] (mailto:support@biginte
 rview.com). Their live team is available are available 7am-4pm CT.
