DESCRIPTION:--------------\nRevised Résumé\n--------------\n\n Overview\
 n---------\n\nYour résumé is a foundational part of searching for intern
 ships and jobs. Now that you have optimized your document as much as possi
 ble using BigInterview's Resume Scan feature\, you'll submit your final do
 cument and prepare for your 1:1 Resume Coaching Session with our team. Thi
 s assignment is designed for you to:\n\n* Receive individualized feedback 
 from a trained coach on areas of your formatting that still need improveme
 nt\n\n* Ensure your résumé formatting looks professional and is ready fo
 r your 1:1 coaching session\n\n* Be able to prioritize talking through cus
 tomizing and adding content in your coaching session\, rather than spendin
 g too much time on formatting adjustments\n\nSubmission Requirements: \n\
 n* Read through and implement your Big Interview Feedback from all 3 secti
 ons of your detailed feedback report.\n\n* Submit a revised résumé that 
 utilizes your Big Interview feedback and one of the approved College of Bu
 siness résumé formats. \n\n* You are REQUIRED to utilize one of the Col
 lege of Business résumé formats.\n\n* Résumés that have not been revis
 ed using one of the approved College of Business formats will be required 
 to resubmit.\n\n* Review all Big Interview and moderator feedback and make
  the necessary changes to your résumé prior to your 1:1 coaching session
 .\n\n* If you score "Not Approved"\, you will be required to revise your r
 ésumé further and resubmit.\n\n  STOP!!!\n\nHave you revised your rés
 umé using one of the approved College of Business résumé formats?\nRés
 umés submitted that do not use an approved College of Business format WIL
 L NOT be accepted\, and you will be required to resubmit your assignment.
   \n\n Resources\n----------\n\nThis assignment aligns with the [Craft 
 Your Resume Videos] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/craft-you
 r-resume-videos-2-2-2) and [Building Your Resume Instructions] (https://ca
 nvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/building-your-resume-instructions-2). I
 f you have not reviewed this content\, go back before you begin. Other res
 ources that may also be useful include resources from the [Student Resume 
 Building Resources] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/folder/St
 udent%20Resources/R%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s) folder:\n\n* [How to Write Strong Bul
 let Statements.pdf] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23679086?
 wrap=1)\n\n* [Adding Project Experiences to Your Resume.pdf] (https://canv
 as.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677285?wrap=1)\n\n* [Resume How-to for A
 ccounting.pdf] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678666?wrap=
 1)\n\n* [Resume How-to for Actuarial Science.pdf] (https://canvas.unl.edu/
 courses/208826/files/23677353?wrap=1)\n\n* [Crafting Your Resume - Experie
 nce Section.pdf] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678264?wra
 p=1)\n\n* [Crafting Your Resume - Additional Resume Sections.pdf] (https:/
 /canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677450?wrap=1)\n\n Grading and Fee
 dback\n---------------------\n\nGrading:\nYou will be graded on the follow
 ing scale:\n\n* Approved: Your résumé is in pretty good shape and genera
 lly meets the course formatting requirements. There may be a few suggested
  revisions for you to make\, but overall\, you are ready for your 1:1 coac
 hing session.\n\n* Not Approved: Your résumé does not meet expectations\
 , and you have some more work to do. You must edit your résumé and resub
 mit within the timeline your moderator provides. You may NOT attend your 1
 :1 coaching session until your document is revised and you have received a
 n "approved" score.\n\nModerator Feedback: \nYour moderator will review y
 our submission and provide feedback on ways to further improve your format
 ting prior to your 1:1 coaching session\, even if you are "Approved" for y
 our coaching session. You are expected to review this feedback and make an
 y requested edits.\n\n FAQs\n-----\n\nI think my résumé looks good. Do 
 I need to make changes? \nYes. Every student should be making updates to 
 their résumé based on the formatting content covered in the Craft Your R
 ésumé videos. It is also required that you utilize one of the [approved 
 College of Business formats] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/
 folder/Resume%20Formats).
