DESCRIPTION:--------------------------------------\n1:1 Résumé Coaching S
 ession Checkpoint\n--------------------------------------\n\n  Overview\n
 ----------\n\nAfter your résumé formatting has gotten to a good place\, 
 it is crucial to write strong bullet statements that sell your skills and 
 experience to organizations. Bullet statement writing can be challenging t
 hough\, so you are required to meet with a trained career coach to talk ab
 out what makes you unique and how you can market yourself to others. This
  assignment is designed for you to:\n\n* Discuss your career goals and how
  to become a competitive applicant for positions\n\n* Receive coaching on 
 how to write strong bullet statements that market yourself effectively fr
 om a trained career coach\n\nSubmission Guidelines:\n\n* Update your résu
 mé formatting using one of the [approved College of Business formats] (ht
 tps://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/Eny90BK084
 9Ap_3EPClwQ1IB83cvffdDKNQPK0RjUUiy_g?e=YDooCf) and complete the [Revised R
 ésumé assignment] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/225
 1666?module_item_id=6205706).\n\n* You must score "Approved" on this assig
 nment prior to attending your 1:1 coaching session.\n\n* Sign-up for your 
 1:1 coaching session with your moderator. You must schedule your appointme
 nt for a day between Monday\, March 30 and Friday\, April 24 unless otherw
 ise notified by your moderator.\n\n* Moderator assignments and direct sche
 duling links can be found below.\n\n* Submit a screenshot (example below) 
 of your scheduled appointment to verify you are signed up.\n\n* Attend you
 r [1:1 Résumé Coaching Session] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/a
 ssignments/2251638) with your moderator before Friday\, April 24 at 5:00pm
  CT.\n\nNote: drop-in coaching session will not fulfill this assignment re
 quirement\, nor will a coaching session with the Business Career Center pr
 ior to taking BSAD 222. You must complete a scheduled coaching session wit
 h your moderator.\n\n  STOP!!! Do not schedule your appointment for a day
  prior to Monday\, March 30th\, unless you have been notified by your mode
 rator that your résumé is approved.\n\n  Resources\n-----------\n\nThis
  assignment is a precursor to the [1:1 Résumé Coaching Session] (https:/
 /canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251638) and [Professional ] (
 https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251660)[Résumé] (http
 s://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251660) assignment. Make s
 ure to review these assignment requirements.[] (https://myplan.unl.edu/res
 ources)\n\n  Instructions\n--------------\n\nStep 1 - Find Your Moderator
 \n----------------------------\n\n* Maris Grabill\, Resume coach for last 
 names A-Co: https://go.unl.edu/marisgrabill \n\n* Jimmy Truong\, Resume c
 oach for last names Cr-La: https://go.unl.edu/jimmytruong\n\n* Gianna Zite
 lla\, Resume coach for last names Le-T: https://go.unl.edu/giannazitella\
 n\n* Kadina Koonce\, Resume coach for last names V-Z:  https://go.unl.edu
 /kadinakoonce\n\nStep 2 - Schedule Your Appointment\n---------------------
 -------------\n\n* Find your moderator from the list above and click the h
 yperlink next to their name. It is critical that you sign-up with the corr
 ect career coach or your appointment will be canceled. \n\n* Click Schedu
 le an Appointment\n [SSH - 1b.PNG] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826
 /files/23677340/preview)\n\n* Choose Resume/Cover Letter from the list of 
 Career Services topic options.\n[InkedSSH - 4a.jpg] (https://canvas.unl.ed
 u/courses/208826/files/23677918/preview)\n  \n\n* Use the calendar to se
 lect a day and time that will work for your schedule. You must schedule yo
 ur appointment for a day between Monday\, March 30 and Friday\, April 24 u
 nless otherwise notified by your moderator.\n[SSH - 5a.jpg] (https://canva
 s.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677590/preview)\n\n* Select the In-Person
  or Virtual Appointment option and any additional details you'd like to di
 scuss during your appointment.\n[SSH - 6a.jpg] (https://canvas.unl.edu/cou
 rses/208826/files/23678099/preview)\n\n* Take a screenshot of your confirm
 ation page which shows the date\, time\, and individual with whom you are 
 scheduled.\n[SSH - 7a.jpg] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23
 679103/preview)\n\n* You will receive a confirmation email to your Huskers
  email address. If you do not receive a confirmation email to your Husker
 s address\, you did not successfully schedule your appointment.\n\nStep 3
  - Submit Confirmation\n----------------------------\n\n* Submit a screens
 hot of your confirmation page which shows the date\, time\, and individual
  with whom you are scheduled. The screenshot MUST include this informatio
 n.\n\n* Your screenshot should look like this (but with your moderator's n
 ame and photo): \n[SSH - 7b.jpg] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/f
 iles/23678064/preview)\n[If you are uncertain how to take a screenshot\, v
 iew instructions here] (https://www.pcmag.com/news/how-to-take-a-screensho
 t-on-any-device).\n\n* Make sure to write down or mark your calendar for w
 hen your appointment is. The system will also automatically send you a re
 minder email beforehand depending on how your notifications are configured
 .\n\nStep 4 - Review the No Show and Cancellation Policy\n----------------
 -----------------------------------\n\nNo Show Policy:\n\n* No shows and l
 ast-minute cancellations for your résumé coaching session are unacceptab
 le and will not be tolerated. You are expected to reschedule appointments 
 at least 24-hours in advance. If you schedule and then fail to show up fo
 r 2 appointments without proactively communicating with your assigned coac
 h\, you will receive a "No Pass".\n\nSick/Emergency Situations:\n\n* In ca
 se of an emergency or if you are sick the day of your appointment\, you ma
 y use Student Success Hub or call 402-472-7272 to reschedule your appointm
 ent. You are also expected to contact your assigned coach directly via Can
 vas messages to let them know what is going on as soon as possible.\n\n  
 Grading and Feedback\n----------------------\n\nGrading: \nThis is a comp
 lete/incomplete assignment. You will receive a complete if you schedule yo
 ur appointment with the correct coach during the timeframe indicated.\n\nN
 ote: If you do not schedule with the correct coach\, you will score an "In
 complete" and be required to resubmit.\n\n  FAQs\n------\n\nTo be added a
 s questions arise.
