DESCRIPTION:-----------------------\nCliftonStrengths Report\n-------------
 ----------\n\n  Overview\n----------\n\nCliftonStrengths for Students is 
 a personalized talent assessment that showcases each individual’s top fi
 ve themes of talent. Understanding your top five themes of talent will all
 ow you to build a professional brand and communicate your unique abilities
  to employers in a clear and memorable manner. This assignment is designed
  for you to:\n\n* Identify your natural talents so you can begin to practi
 ce them and hone them into Strengths\n\n* Understand your CliftonStrengths
  results and the role they play in worker engagement\n\n* Begin to conside
 r the impact that your Strengths have upon how you make decisions and plan
 s\n\nSubmission Requirements:\n\nSubmit your CliftonStrengths Top 5 Report
  or CliftonStrengths for Students to Canvas by downloading it from the [Cl
 iftonStrengths for Students website] (https://www.strengthsquest.com/home.
 aspx). Review the detailed instructions below to see how to access your re
 sults if you have previously taken the assessment or how to redeem the acc
 ess code that will be emailed to you if you have not taken the assessment 
 before.\n\n   STOP!!! You should not pay for a CliftonStrengths access c
 ode. Review the assignment instructions below.  \n\n  Resources\n------
 -----\n\nThis assignment aligns with the [Showcase Your Skills & Strengths
  module] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/modules/701593). If you h
 ave not reviewed the module content\, go back to it before you begin. Othe
 r resources that may also be useful include:\n\n*\n\n* [Strengths Quick Re
 ference Card] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677296?wrap=1
 ) - Brief description of all 34 themes \n\n* [Gallup's Theme Thursday] (h
 ttps://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLxDaK7wIyw947k6hxvoPa4-DYMbgJZYNt) -
  a live video event that provides a deeper context regarding strengths\n\
 n* [CliftonStrengths Theme Descriptors ] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/2
 08826/files/23677454?wrap=1)- describe your top themes to others effective
 ly using your own words\n\n* [Bring & Need Descriptions] (https://www.gal
 lup.com/cliftonstrengths/en/655616/bring-need-statements.aspx) - what do 
 your themes need from or bring to a group compared to others\n\n  Instruc
 tions\n--------------\n\n* If you took BSAD 111\, BSAD 111s\, or have take
 n the CliftonStrengths (StrengthsQuest) assessment previously\, you DO NOT
  need to take the assessment again and will submit your previous results (
 see instructions labeled Accessing Previous Assessment Results to submit 
 your report correctly)\n\n* If you have not taken the assessment before an
 d indicated a need for a code on the Pre-Class Survey\, a code will only b
 e provided to students who do not have BSAD 111 or 111s on their transcrip
 t.\n\nAccessing Previous Assessment Results\n-----------------------------
 --------\n\n* Go to https://www.strengthsquest.com/home.aspx. \n\n* Click
  "Sign In" at the top of the page and log in with the same email address a
 nd password you used to create your account.\n\n* If you need assistance l
 ogging in to your account\, call the CliftonStrengths Help Desk at 1-888-2
 11-4049 or email [StrengthsQuestHelp@gallup.com] (mailto:StrengthsQuestHel
 p@gallup.com).\n\n* Scroll down on your dashboard to the "Reports" section
  and select the "CliftonStrengths Top 5 Report" or "CliftonStrengths for S
 tudents Report" from the list of options.\n[Strengths Assignment .png] (ht
 tps://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678343/preview)\n\n* Read your
  report\, download and save a PDF copy to your computer\, and upload the r
 eport to Canvas.\n\n* Note: the correct report type will typically be abou
 t 16 pages.\n\nRedeeming an Access Code\n------------------------\n\nWhen 
 taking the Pre-Class Survey\, you should have indicated that you had not p
 reviously taken the CliftonStrengths assessment. If you did so and are eli
 gible to receive a code (i.e.\, it was verified that you have not taken BS
 AD 111 or 111s)\, a code will be emailed to you before the assignment dead
 line.\n\n* Check the email address you listed in the Pre-Class Survey. You
  may need to check your clutter\, junk\, and/or spam folders if you do not
  see a message in your inbox.\n\n* Go to https://www.strengthsquest.com/ho
 me.aspx and select "Redeem Access Code" at the top of the page.\n[Redeem 
 Strengths Access Code] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/236776
 90/download)  \n\n* Complete your registration and create your account. S
 elect your preferred language.\n\n* Note: international students are encou
 raged to select their native language\n\n* Select "Take the CliftonStrengt
 hs assessment" and read the directions carefully.\n\n* Finalize your demog
 raphic information.\n\n* Take the assessment. If you lose your internet co
 nnection\, you will be able to sign back in and be automatically returned 
 to where you left off.\n\n* Scroll down on your dashboard to the "Reports"
  section and select the "CliftonStrengths Top 5 Report" or "CliftonStrengt
 hs for Students Report" from the list of options.  \n\n* Read your repor
 t\, download and save a PDF copy to your computer\, and upload the report 
 to Canvas.\n\n* Note: the correct report type will typically be about 16 p
 ages.\n\n  Grading and Feedback\n----------------------\n\nGrading:\nThis
  is a complete/incomplete assignment. You will receive a complete if you 
 submit the correct report type.\n\nNote: If you score an "Incomplete"\, yo
 u are required to review your moderator's feedback and resubmit within the
  timeline provided.\n\n  FAQs\n------\n\nI have taken the assessment befo
 re. How do I access my old account? \nReview the instructions above under
  "Accessing Previous Assessment Results" for details on how to access your
  previous assessment results.\n\nHelp! I forgot my password or am having t
 echnical difficulty accessing my old account. \nPlease call the CliftonSt
 rengths Help Desk at 1-888-211-4049 or email [StrengthsQuestHelp@gallup.co
 m] (mailto:StrengthsQuestHelp@gallup.com). We are unable to provide techni
 cal assistance. You can also revisit your BSAD 111 Canvas class and upload
  the report you submitted there. Please email your moderator to let them k
 now your document may look a bit different than the one asked for in advan
 ce. \n\nI already took the assessment\, but I want to take it again becau
 se I feel like my results are not accurate. \nCodes are only issued to st
 udents who have not taken the CliftonStrengths assessment before. If you w
 ould like to retake the assessment\, please visit my.gallup.com to purchas
 e a new code. 
