DESCRIPTION:-----------------\nFocus2 Assessment\n-----------------\n\n  O
 verview\n----------\n\nKnowing yourself is a critical component in choosin
 g a major and career path as it leads to higher engagement and job satisfa
 ction. This assignment is designed for you to:\n\n* Reflect on your intere
 sts\, skills\, and values\n\n* Identify majors and career paths that conne
 ct to your interests\, skills\, and values\n\n* Begin to develop your prof
 essional brand and practice communicating it to others\n\nSubmission Requi
 rements:\n\nSubmit your Focus2 Assessment portfolio by completing the 5 re
 quired assessments\, 5 Saved Occupations\, and downloading your results fr
 om the [Focus2 website] (https://go.unl.edu/focus2). Review the detailed i
 nstructions below to review which assessments to complete\, how to access 
 them\, and download your portfolio.\n\n  Resources\n-----------\n\nThis a
 ssignment aligns with the [Showcase Your Skills & Strengths module videos/
 readings] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/showcase-your-skill
 s-and-strengths-module-videos-slash-readings-2-2). If you have not review
 ed the module content\, go back to it before you begin.\n\nFocus 2 Overvi
 ew and Walk-through Video\n\n  Instructions\n--------------\n\n*\n\nStep 
 1 - Create Your Focus2 Account\n-----------------------------------\n\nIf 
 you have never accessed Focus2 before\, you will need to create an account
 .\n\n* Go to https://go.unl.edu/focus2 and select "Register" to create an
  account.\n\n* Enter "huskers" into the Access Code box and then continue 
 to fill out your registration information.\n[Focus2 - 1.JPG] (https://canv
 as.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678002/preview)\n  \n\n* Complete the 
 Account Information section by choosing "Class Assignment" for how you lea
 rned about Focus2 and then selecting "BSAD 222".\n[Focus2 - 2.JPG] (https:
 //canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678795/preview)\n  \n\n* Click "
 Continue" and a confirmation that your account was created will appear at 
 the top of the page.\n\nStep 2 - Complete the Assessments\n---------------
 ------------------\n\n* Go to https://go.unl.edu/focus2 and login.\n\n* Se
 lect the assessment you want to take and read the directions carefully.\n\
 n* You must complete the following 5 assessments:\n\n* My Career Planning 
 Involvement\n\n* Work Interest Assessment\n\n* Values Assessment\n\n* Skil
 ls Assessment\n\n* Leisure Assessment\n\n  [Focus2 - 3.JPG] (https://canv
 as.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677883/preview)[Focus2 - 4.JPG] (https:/
 /canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677427/download)\n\nStep 3 - Save Y
 our Occupations\n------------------------------\n\n* After viewing your re
 sults on 1 or more of your assessments\, select the save button (while in 
 Card View) for 5 or more careers of interest. As a reminder\, your career 
 results are listed in alphabetical order\, not rank order based on your re
 sults. [image.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677997/d
 ownload)\n\n* A faster way to get to careers of interest is by scrolling p
 ast your assessment to the "Exploring Your Options Section" and selecting 
 "Explore Occupations by Job Family". [image.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/c
 ourses/208826/files/23677815/download)\n\n* Then select a career title and
  then the "Heart" icon. [image.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826
 /files/23677419/download)\n\nStep 4 - Upload Your Report\n----------------
 -----------\n\n* Scroll to the bottom of your Focus2 dashboard to the sect
 ion called "[Your Name]'s Reports" and select "View Your Report".\n[Focus2
  - 5-1.JPG] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23677597/preview)
 \n\n* Select the 5 required assessments and your Saved Occupations Report\
 , then click "Continue".\n[image.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/2088
 26/files/23679005/preview)\n  \n\n* Download your customized report and 
 submit the PDF to Canvas.[Focus2-PDF.JPG] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/
 208826/files/23677258/download)\n\n  Grading and Feedback\n--------------
 --------\n\nGrading:\nThis is a complete/incomplete assignment. You will 
 receive a complete if your submitted portfolio includes all five of the re
 quired assessments.\n\nNote: If you score an "Incomplete"\, you are requir
 ed to review your moderator's feedback and resubmit within the timeline pr
 ovided.
