DESCRIPTION:---------------\nCareer Research\n---------------\n\n  Overvie
 w\n----------\n\nCareer research is an important part of the career planni
 ng process as it helps you to make informed career decisions\, build confi
 dence in your chosen career path\, and ask professionals in your area of i
 nterest educated questions. This discussion is designed for you to:\n\n* I
 dentify and explore careers\, organizations\, or industries through resear
 ch to ensure a broad understanding and awareness of existing career paths 
 and opportunities\n\n* Develop confidence in your chosen path by exploring
  its connection to your interests\, skills\, values\, and strengths\n\n* R
 eview your peers' research to inspire new insights\, create networking opp
 ortunities\, and enhance our collective grasp of career options.\n\nTo mee
 t submission requirements\, your post must include (1) your attached 7+ pa
 ge document of your career research results from the widget (2) answers to
  all the required prompts.\n\n \n\n  Getting Started:\n\n* STEP 1: Open 
 the [Career Exploration Widget] (https://partyrock.aws/u/KadK/ahBy_TAAK/Ca
 reer-Exploration-Widget) \n\n* If this does not work or you're asked to l
 og in and do not wish to\, please feel free to open your AI system of choi
 ce and use the prompts noted [here] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826
 /files/23678825?wrap=1).\n\n* If you prefer not to use AI in any capacity\
 , please contact your primary instructor for an alternative paper assignme
 nt.\n\n* STEP 2: Fill out the first 4 boxes. Insert your major (or one of 
 the job titles you saved in your Focus 2)\, work location of interest\, 3 
 industry interests or strengths\, and select 3 career values.\n\n* STEP 3:
  After reviewing the new list of options insert one career of interest fro
 m the list or your original job title from the beginning in the "Career of
  Interest" section to generate your detailed report.\n\n* STEP 4: After re
 ading the first portion of your report\, insert a current position (Barist
 a\, Cashier\, Student\, Marketing Specialist) and your desired career to g
 enerate steps you might consider to make the transition.\n\n* STEP 5: Sele
 ct the 3 horizontal bars in the top right corner of the widget and “Expo
 rt as a Word document” to get a 7-12 page [copy of the full report] (htt
 ps://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678289?wrap=1) (sample report l
 inked). Upload this document as an attachment so your peers can see the su
 ggestions and feedback provided.\n\n* If you used a different AI engine in
 stead of the PartyRock tool\, please select the "Share" or "Copy" button a
 t the top or bottom of the thread (Every question and answer should be for
 matted in a Word Document) and attach that document. You can also ask the 
 system to summarize every question and response into an uploadable documen
 t.\n\n* STEP 6: Write a reflection that addresses ALL the prompts below\; 
 strong reflections will be a minimum of 400 words.\n\n \n\n  Required Pr
 ompts to Answer for the Discussion Board\n\n* Alignment: What industries\,
  strengths\, impacts\, or values are of the highest importance to you when
  considering career options and why?\n\n* New Career Titles: List 2-5 job 
 titles\, career paths\, or related jobs that stood out to you\, and why. W
 ere there any that surprised you and seemed like a good fit?\n\n* Career T
 itle Selected for Exploration: Which career title did you choose to input 
 into the "Career of Interest" line to conduct more research?\n\n* Benefits
  and Challenges: Which benefits and challenges provided by your report cau
 ght your attention or prompted further thought? How could these factors in
 fluence your future career decisions?\n\n* Skills: Which of the listed ski
 lls from your report do you want to prioritize most before graduation\, an
 d why?\n\n* Transition: What are 2 suggestions or ideas you got from the T
 ransitioning from Job A to Job B section. Why did these stand out or feel 
 relevant?\n\n* Additional Research: Share a link from a YouTube Video\, Li
 nkedIn video\, or Instagram Reel regarding "things to know" or "day in the
  life" related to this career\, and 1 takeaway you got from it.\n\n* Caree
 r Exploration: What have you done so far to explore what careers exist an
 d what you might want to do?\n\n* Alternatively\, if you are uncertain abo
 ut your career goals\, what is making you feel stuck? Why?\n\n* Action Ite
 m: What is one thing that you could do in the next 3 months to feel more c
 onfident in your career selection?\n\n \n\n  Review Peer Posts\n\n* Rev
 iew 2-3 of your peers reflections to gain additional ideas for career expl
 oration or consideration.\n\n* You may be asked to reflect on your values 
 and career selections with your peers in class\, so you'll want to have re
 viewed a few for richer discussion. \n\n* No peer replies are required\, 
 but you're welcome to leave a comment if you like or want to connect with 
 a peer that has similar interests. 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Career Research: Exploring Your Career Options Discussion [BSAD-222
 -951.1261]
