DESCRIPTION:[BSAD222 Banner - June 2017-1-1.png] (https://canvas.unl.edu/co
 urses/208826/files/23678774/preview)\n\nAs you update your resume and begi
 n your job/career exploration\, consider starting with Handshake. Handshak
 e is a specialized online platform designed specifically for college stude
 nts and recent graduates to find entry-level jobs\, internships\, career e
 vents\, and resources. While LinkedIn has a broader professional network\,
  Handshake emphasizes campus-based opportunities\, making it a valuable to
 ol for students seeking to kickstart their careers on campus or nationwide
 .\n\nBy effectively using Handshake alongside LinkedIn (as you'll learn mo
 re about in 333)\, you can increase your visibility to potential employers
  and enhance your overall career exploration and job search.\n\nCompletion
  Requirements: \n\n* Review the [Handshake Resource Page] (https://canvas
 .unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/handshake-resource-page) and the videos to d
 emonstrate your understanding of the platform\, and correctly answer the t
 wo knowledge-check questions.\n\n* Submit a screenshot of your [Handshake
  profile] (https://unl.joinhandshake.com/) showing:\n\n*\n\n* Professional
  headshot.\n\n* Looking for: Types of roles\, industries\, and locations y
 ou're looking for opportunities in.\n\n* About: Short summary including yo
 ur interests\, strengths\, skills\, or key experience.\n\n[Screenshot of H
 andshake profile their profile photo on the left then on the right their s
 elections for what they are "looking for" and a brief About section highli
 ghting their skills and experience.] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/20882
 6/files/24136797/preview)
