DESCRIPTION:-------------------------------------\n Career Growth Strategy
  & Action Plan\n-------------------------------------\n\n Overview\n-----
 ----\n\nBuilding on the valuable insights you gained from your recent care
 er research assignment\, it's now time to envision yourself in various car
 eers of interest by building a Growth Strategy and Action Plan. This assig
 nment is meant to help you chart multiple courses for your future career a
 nd map out action steps that prepare you for uncertainty and change.\n\nUs
 ing the provided link\, you'll consider and assess three unique careers:\n
 \n* Career 1: This plan focuses on refining a potential career path that i
 nterests you. You'll develop a detailed action plan tailored to achieving 
 your goals within this framework.\n\n* Career 2: This option lets you expl
 ore a completely different career path that piques your curiosity. You'll 
 identify the skills and steps needed to navigate a new idea.\n\n* Career 3
 : This option can allow you to explore dream careers or consider what you 
 might want in your future after careers 1 and 2. Considering your third op
 tion can help you identify your passions and priorities beyond the now.\n\
 nBy exploring these diverse paths\, you'll gain valuable insights and refi
 ne your career goals with greater clarity. \n\nHow to complete this assig
 nment:\n\n* Select the following link to begin: [Career Growth Strategy & 
 Action Plan Assignment] (https://unlcba.az1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_cHAg
 otPfoHsedJc)\n\n* Plan to spend at least 30 minutes on this activity. Seve
 ral questions include character minimums and require thoughtful reflection
  to fully engage with the process.\n\n* After completing the form\, downlo
 ad the PDF that includes all of your responses.\n\n* Upload that PDF to Ca
 nvas for grading. \n\n  STOP.\n\nPlease keep in mind that all elements o
 f the worksheet must be completed in full\nSubmissions missing content\, i
 ntentional thought\, or with careers too similar will be returned for resu
 bmission.\n\n Resources\n----------\n\nSample PDF Submission (Preview Ass
 ignment Questions)\n\n* Due to the PDF format for student submissions\, yo
 ur document should be about 20-23 pages in length\n\nList of action items\
 , experiences\, campus organizations\, technical skills\, etc. to consider
  including in your plans.\n\n* [Resources to Develop Your Plan] (https://c
 anvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/resources-to-develop-your-plan-2-2-2-2)
 \n\n Guidelines\n-----------\n\nOutline Your Approach & Consider Your Min
 dset\n---------------------------------------------\n\nAs you take note of
  the possibilities\, also consider how your current stage of life and mind
 set play a role in approaching your planning and strategy development. Her
 e's how your perspective can influence your initial exploration:\n\n* Conf
 ident and Focused\, typically on 1 career/goal:\n\n* Developing Career #1 
 might be easy for you since you already have a vision in mind. Consider:\n
 \n* What other careers provide work environments I'd thrive in?\n\n* What 
 haven't I thought of in a while or that unexpected "thing" others have tol
 d me I'm really good at?\n\n* What industries or fields are growing that m
 ight offer unexpected opportunities?\n\n* Content with your major/career b
 ut Open:\n\n* Building Career #1 as a secure option and Career #2 as a sec
 ondary option might come naturally to you. Consider:\n\n* What possibiliti
 es have I considered but have not yet acted on?\n\n* What industries have 
 been introduced/exposed to but would like to explore further?\n\n* Don't h
 esitate to consider majors beyond Business for inspiration. Look back at F
 ocus2's "What Can I Do If I Majored In..." tab or your career research res
 ults for a list of possible careers by major.\n\n* Uncertain and Exploring
 :\n\n* Creating all 3 lives might feel like a blank canvas\, but that is a
  good thing! Consider:\n\n* A career that feels secure\, a career that see
 ms interesting\, and a career that seems risky but rewarding\n\n* What are
  the careers of family members and friends? What populations do I wish to 
 impact? What problems do I hope to solve or make positive contributions to
 ?\n\n* See the plans as a space to brainstorm your "what if" scenarios. "W
 hat if I tried this major\, and how would I hope it would play out?"\n\n* 
 Don't hesitate to consider majors beyond Business for inspiration. Look ba
 ck at Focus2's "What Can I Do If I Majored In..." tab or your career resea
 rch results for a list of possible careers by major.\n\nSelecting Careers 
 & Strategizing Your Goals\n-------------------------------------------\n\n
 Imagine 3 different career possibilities and the different experiences\, g
 oals\, and milestones that might be associated with each.\n\nSelect a Care
 er:\n\n* Consider careers in your current major\, adjacent to it\, and dif
 ferent from it\, as well as the "I would if I could" career.\n\n* Use your
  Focus 2 results or look back at the related careers provided by your care
 er research assignment to brainstorm ideas if you are having trouble consi
 dering 3 different plans.\n\nBuild Your Plan:\n\nFor each year in Career #
 1\, please use the [Resources to Develop Your Plan ] (https://canvas.unl.e
 du/courses/208822/pages/resources-to-develop-your-plan-2-2-2-2)and the top
 ics below for the career-related elements:\n\n* Career Goals:\n\n* Outline
  your career progression within each distinct life path:\n\n* Apply for a 
 X internship near home/out of state\n\n* Shadow professionals at dream com
 panies in your chosen field.\n\n* Earn a promotion to a specific job title
  with increased responsibility.\n\n* Start your own business and outline y
 our entrepreneurial journey.\n\n* Speak at industry conferences to share y
 our expertise.\n\n* Achieve specific sales targets if you're pursuing a sa
 les-oriented career.\n\n* Publish research findings in academic journals i
 f you're on a research-focused path.\n\n* Pursue an MBA or other advanced 
 degree to enhance your qualifications.\n\n* Major Specific Considerations:
 \n\n* [05 - Major Specific Planning Considerations] (https://uofnebraska.s
 harepoint.com/:x:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/IQCc4BrZZ6m0SqskAubodIDQAUuj9
 VJS99g8gxLvBR_BwIw?e=RUW9gB)\n\n* Social/Extracurricular Experiences:\n\n*
  Consider life-changing events that can shape your skills and perspectives
 :\n\n* Join a relevant student organization (e.g.\, Engineering club for a
 n engineering path).\n\n* Study abroad to gain a global perspective and po
 tentially language skills.\n\n* Engage in impactful community service proj
 ects.\n\n* Participate in case study competitions to test your problem-sol
 ving abilities.\n\n* Secure an internship at a company you admire\, gainin
 g hands-on experience.\n\n* Attend professional development events to enha
 nce your knowledge and skillset.\n\n* Networking:\n\n* Build your professi
 onal network to gain valuable insights and open doors to opportunities:\n\
 n* Conduct research with a professor or a research institution.\n\n* Conne
 ct with professionals working in your field at industry events or online p
 latforms like LinkedIn.\n\n* Follow up with company recruiters you've met 
 during interviews.\n\n* Find a mentor in your desired industry to provide 
 guidance and support.\n\n* Reach out to industry leaders for informational
  interviews to learn about their career paths.\n\n* Academic/Passion Proje
 ct Goals:\n\n* Identify specific technical skills needed for your desired 
 career path and outline your plan to acquire them:\n\n* Take the Union Pac
 ific/Ameritas Project-based course.\n\n* Take an elective course in a comp
 letely different college or department that sparks your curiosity.\n\n* Ea
 rn relevant certifications (e.g.\, project management certification).\n\n*
  Pass career-related exams (e.g.\, LSAT\, CPA exam).\n\n* Master specific 
 software programs (e.g.\, coding languages for software development\, data
  analysis software for research).\n\n* Start a personal blog or online por
 tfolio dedicated to a specific interest.\n\n* Develop a personal photograp
 hy or videography project with a specific theme or goal.\n\nCrafting Your 
 Six Word Headline\n-------------------------------\n\nPick a 6-Word Headli
 ne for each plan.\n\n* The headline should capture the core essence of eac
 h unique life path you've outlined.\n\n* Consider the key elements that di
 fferentiate each path:\n\n* Career Focus: Is it technology\, education\, s
 ocial impact\, or something else?\n\n* Work Environment: Is it corporate\,
  entrepreneurial\, international\, or research-oriented?\n\n* Personal Goa
 ls: Are travel\, language learning\, or family priorities woven into the p
 lan?\n\nHere are a few examples:\n\n* "Marketing Expert and International 
 Brand Builder"\n\n* "Tech Startup Founder: Code\, Launch\, Disrupt"\n\n* "
 Global Entrepreneur: Build Bridges Break Barriers"\n\n* "Family First\, Bu
 ild Memories\, Create Legacy"\n\n* "Travel Blogger\, Explore\, Share\, Ins
 pire Others"\n\n* "All In - The Silicon Valley Story"\n\nGrading and Feedb
 ack\n--------------------\n\nGrading: \nYou will be graded on the followi
 ng scale:\n\n* Complete: Your submitted PDF includes all required sections
  and demonstrates thoughtful engagement with the Career Growth Strategy an
 d Action Plan. Your action steps and reflections are realistic\, specific\
 , and clearly connected to your interests\, strengths\, and values.\n\n* I
 ncomplete: Your submission is missing one or more required components\, do
 es not meet the minimum character requirements\, or lacks sufficient detai
 l to demonstrate meaningful engagement. You will be asked to revise and re
 submit within the timeline provided by your moderator. \n\n FAQs\n-----\
 n\nHow long will this take?\n\n* Plan for at least 30 minutes. Many questi
 ons include reflection and minimum character requirements\, so give yourse
 lf uninterrupted time.\n\nCan I leave and come back later?\n\n* Yes\, as l
 ong as you use the same device/browser and do not clear your cache. It’s
  recommended that you complete the assignment in one sitting if possible.\
 n\nWhy can’t I move forward?\n\n* Some questions require a minimum numbe
 r of selections\, a minimum character count\, and/or all required fields t
 o be completed. Make sure you’ve met all instructions before moving to t
 he next page.\n\nWhat if I’m unsure about my career path?\n\n* That’s 
 completely normal. This assignment is designed to help you explore possibi
 lities\, not commit to a final decision.\n\nWhat if I have technical issue
 s?\n\n* Take a screenshot and contact your moderator as soon as possible.
