DESCRIPTION:---------------------------\n1:1 Résumé Coaching Session\n---
 ------------------------\n\n  Overview\n----------\n\nAfter your résumé
  formatting has gotten to a good place\, it is crucial to write strong bul
 let statements that sell your skills and experience to organizations. Bull
 et statement writing can be challenging though\, so you are required to me
 et with a trained career coach to talk about what makes you unique and how
  you can market yourself to others. This assignment is designed for you t
 o:\n\n* Discuss your career goals and how to become a competitive applican
 t for positions\n\n* Receive coaching on how to write strong bullet statem
 ents that market yourself effectively from a trained career coach\n\nSubmi
 ssion Requirements:\n\nYou are expected to attend a coaching session with 
 your assigned moderator\, either in-person or virtually. Prior to your coa
 ching session\, you must score "approved" on your [Revised Résumé assig
 nment] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251666?module_i
 tem_id=6205706) and complete your [Résumé Coaching Session Checkpoint] (
 https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251640). \n\nYou will 
 not submit anything for your coaching session\, but must attend between Mo
 nday\, March 30th and Friday\, April 24th. It is expected that you come pr
 epared to your session with an updated version of your revised résumé\, 
 either electronic or printed\, and that you are actively engaged in the co
 aching session.\n\nImportant Notes:\n\n* No shows and last-minute cancella
 tions for your résumé coaching session are unacceptable and will not be 
 tolerated. You are expected to reschedule appointments at least 24-hours i
 n advance. If you schedule and then fail to show up for 2 appointments wit
 hout proactively communicating with your assigned coach\, you will receive
  a "No Pass".\n\n* Drop-in coaching session will not fulfill this assignm
 ent requirement\, nor will a coaching session with the Business Career Cen
 ter prior to taking BSAD 222. You must complete a scheduled coaching sessi
 on with your moderator.\n\n  Resources\n-----------\n\nThis assignment al
 igns with the [Résumé Coaching Session Checkpoint] (https://canvas.unl.e
 du/courses/208826/assignments/2251640) and is a precursor to the [Professi
 onal Résumé assignment] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignme
 nts/2251660).  Make sure to review these assignment requirements.\n\n  I
 nstructions\n--------------\n\nStep 1 - Sign-up\n----------------\n\nRevie
 w the [Résumé Coaching Session Checkpoint] (https://canvas.unl.edu/cour
 ses/208826/assignments/2251640) for instructions on how to schedule your 
 coaching session with your moderator. Once your appointment is scheduled\,
  remember to document your date and time.\n\nNote: Your coaching session m
 ust be scheduled between Monday\, March 30th and Friday\, April 24th. You 
 must have a score of "approved" on your Revised Résumé assignment before
  attending your coaching session.\n\nStep 2 - Prepare\n----------------\n\
 nEnsure you are prepared for your coaching session by following these step
 s:\n\n* Review your moderator's feedback on your [Revised Résumé assignm
 ent] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251666?module_ite
 m_id=6205706) and make revisions prior to your coaching session.\n\n* When
  you schedule your coaching session\, you will receive a confirmation emai
 l to your Huskers email account. This message will include directions ab
 out how to attend your appointment depending on the location you have chos
 en (in-person or virtual).\n\n* Review the Craft Your Résumé videos (par
 ticularly those focused on bullet statements) and the required readings fo
 r Module 5 to refresh yourself on expectations for strong bullet statement
 s.\n\n* Come prepared with a printed or electronic version of your résum
 é.\n\nStep 3 (VIRTUAL APPTS ONLY) - Review Virtual Best Practices\n------
 -----------------------------------------------------\n\nZoom Preparations
  Prior to Your Meeting:\n\n* [Download the desktop version of Zoom] (https
 ://unl.zoom.us/download).\n\n* If you are a Mac user\, adjust your securit
 y settings to permit Zoom to operate effectively.\n\n* Go into "Security &
  Privacy" on your Mac and click "zoom.us". You can [review detailed instru
 ctions on allowing permissions here] (https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/art
 icles/360016688031-Using-the-Zoom-Client-and-Zoom-Rooms-with-macOS#h_d9e25
 2a8-4fa0-494b-b019-03c3c735bace1).\n\nAccessing Your Zoom Session:\n\n* Wh
 en you schedule your coaching session\, you will receive a confirmation em
 ail to your Huskers email account. This email will contain the Zoom link 
 that you will need to access your coaching session. \n\n* You will be adm
 itted into a "virtual waiting room" when logging on Zoom so you do not i
 nterrupt a current appointment. Your coach will admit you to the session w
 hen they are available\; please be patient.\n\nTechnology Tips - Sharing Y
 our Screen:\n\n* Have your résumé and any supplemental materials pulled 
 up on your computer. You will be expected to share your screen with your c
 oach.\n\n* Once admitted to the session\, audio and video icons can be fou
 nd along the bottom of your screen. These control your webcam\, audio\, an
 d microphone settings.\n[Audio/video controls - Zoom] (https://canvas.unl.
 edu/courses/208826/files/23677226/preview)\n\n* When prompted\, share your
  screen with your coach by selecting the green "Share Screen" button and
  then share your desktop\, which should contain your résumé. \n[Zoom - 
 Share Screen] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/files/23678168/previe
 w)  \n[Select screen to share] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/fil
 es/23677701/preview)  \n\n* During your coaching session\, your coach may
  request control of your screen to make quick edits or coach you through h
 ow to write strong bullet statements. Approve this request. You may also
  turn over control manually by enabling the "Remote Control" feature you
 rself.\n[Zoom - Turn over remote control] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/
 208826/files/23677901/preview)  \n\nStep 4 - Review the No Show & Sick Po
 licies\n-------------------------------------------\n\nNo Show Policy:\n\n
 * No shows and last-minute cancellations for your résumé coaching sessio
 n are unacceptable and will not be tolerated. You are expected to reschedu
 le appointments at least 24-hours in advance. If you schedule and then fa
 il to show up for 2 appointments without proactively communicating with yo
 ur assigned coach\, you will receive a "No Pass".\n\nSick/Emergency Situat
 ions:\n\n* In case of an emergency or if you are sick the day of your appo
 intment\, you may use Student Success Hub or call 402-472-7272 to reschedu
 le your appointment. You are also expected to contact your assigned coach 
 directly via Canvas messages to let them know what is going on as soon as 
 possible.\n\n  Grading and Feedback\n----------------------\n\nGrading: 
 \nYou will receive either a "Complete" or an "Incomplete" for this assignm
 ent based on whether you attend your 1:1 coaching session.\n\n* If you sch
 edule and then fail to show up for 2 appointments without proactively comm
 unicating with your assigned coach\, you will receive a "No Pass".\n\n* If
  you do not complete your coaching session by the assigned due date\, you 
 will receive a "No Pass" for the course.\n\n  FAQs\n------\n\nTo be added
  as questions arise.
SEQUENCE:0
