DESCRIPTION:***********************************************\nGEOG 155 Major
  Assignment: Notes from the Field\n***************************************
 ********\n\n \n\nThis course lends itself to the world around you as soon
  as you learn about it in class or lab. This assignment aims to help you c
 onnect what you’re learning about in the classroom and lab to the world 
 around you. Also\, this assignment seeks to build your skills regarding th
 e synthesis of information into a digestible format\, or report.\n\n \n\n
 Points available: 100\n\nDue date: April 24th\, 11:59pm\n\n \n\nInstructi
 ons:\n\nTake a photo (or photos) of something you’ve learned about from 
 each “unit” of our semester.  Then\, write 100 words (maximum) about 
 the photo and how it relates to what you learned about in class\, lab\, or
  in your text.\n\n \n\nUnit 1:\n\n* What is Geography?\n\n* Seasonality\n
 \n* Mapping\, electromagnetic spectrum\, GIS\n\n* Introduction to the atmo
 sphere\n\n* Weather and climate\n\n* Temperature and insolation\n\n* Atmos
 pheric pressure\, circulation\, and wind\n\n \n\nUnit 2:\n\n* Atmospheric
  moisture\n\n* Atmospheric disturbance\n\n* Climate change / Paleo climate
 \n\n* Climatic zones and types\n\n* The Hydrosphere / Groundwater\n\n \n\
 nUnit 3:\n\n* Fluvial processes / River systems and landforms\n\n* Biosphe
 re / Flora and fauna\n\n* Dynamic earth / Rock cycle\n\n* Volcanoes\, eart
 hquakes\, and plate tectonics\n\n* Cryosphere\, glacial landforms\n\n \n\
 nYou’re expected to make this report look nice\, and as if you were hand
 ing it out in a presentation in your future career.\n\n \n\nHow you’ll 
 be graded:\n\nEach photo and write up: 30 points\n\nOverall layout and des
 ign: 10 points\n\n \n\nReminder of required items:\n\n \n\n* Photo that 
 you took from each unit\n\n* Write up below the photo explaining how the p
 hoto relates to this class\n\n* Cover page that includes a minimum of your
  name\, date and the project title\, “Notes from the Field”\, automati
 c -5 if missing a cover page
