CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:-------------------\nProfessional Résumé\n-------------------
 \n\n  Overview\n----------\n\nYour résumé is a foundational part of sea
 rching for internships and jobs. To be a competitive applicant for positio
 ns\, it is critical for you to be able to effectively describe your past e
 xperiences through your bullet statements. This assignment is designed for
  you to:\n\n* Showcase you know how to effectively communicate your skills
  through bullet statement writing\n\n* Receive individualized feedback on 
 your document from a trained career coach\n\n* Ensure your résumé is rea
 dy to be utilized for scholarships\, part-time jobs\, and internship appli
 cations\n\nSubmission Requirements: \n\nRevise your résumé based on you
 r moderator's feedback and the instructions and rubric below. It is requir
 ed that you make additional edits after your coaching session as we cannot
  address every bullet statement during your 45-minute meeting. These edits
  should include all revisions that your coach mentioned as well as applyin
 g the information you learned to bullet statements that you and your moder
 ator did not have a chance to specifically address. Submit the updated ver
 sion of your résumé to Canvas.\n\n   STOP!!! Have you carefully review
 ed the rubric and made updates to your résumé based on feedback received
  in your coaching session?\nRemember that you must score at least an "Almo
 st Ready" in EVERY category of the rubric or you will be required to revis
 e and resubmit. Save yourself time and make changes now.\n\n  Resources\
 n-----------\n\nThis assignment aligns with the [Craft Your R] (https://ca
 nvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/craft-your-resume-videos-2-2-2)[ésumé 
 videos] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/craft-your-resume-vid
 eos-2-2-2) and the [Target Your Brand module] (https://canvas.unl.edu/cour
 ses/208826/modules/701599). If you have not reviewed this content\, go bac
 k before you begin. Other resources that may also be useful include:\n\n* 
 [How to Write Bullet Statements] (https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:b:/s
 /UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/ERkDtkVSzUNGoZaQZx4mi-cBtzmbbXp4v9_6NytjxIY_jg?e
 =eigR5w)\n\n* [Bullet Statement Development Worksheet] (https://uofnebrask
 a.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/EQ7BbpCIj5ZPt994NDvpJIkBjy
 Ntjtlzz29YT2jQAeGoNw?e=2XlpjD)\n\n* [ Industry Specific Keyword Resources]
  (https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/Eur2ca
 o1mltFsekKNMSHuA0BzaH7ewSziXfj9b4F9jjJxA?e=Whjku8)  - incorporate action
  verbs and keywords geared toward a specific industry\n\n  Instructions\n
 --------------\n\nStep 1 - Review Tailoring Options\n---------------------
 ------------\n\nAs you apply for future positions\, it is important to rem
 ember that a résumé is never finished and that you should tailor your do
 cument for each individual role. To help you get started on this\, you hav
 e two options when creating your Professional Résumé. \n\n* Option 1: C
 reate a universal résumé which you can edit further in the future. If yo
 u are uncertain of your career plans\, you can write a general résumé to
  showcase your experiences by communicating commonly sought after transfer
 able skills (verbal and written communication\, teamwork\, problem solving
 \, leadership\, etc.).\n\n* Option 2: Tailor your résumé toward a speci
 fic industry\, job function\, or position. This is a great option if you k
 now what type of career you want to pursue in the future or are actively a
 pplying for positions. Incorporate keywords based on the industry or job f
 unction which you are interested in.\n\nStep 2 - Résumé Formatting and A
 ppearance\n-----------------------------------------\n\nThe overall appear
 ance of your  résumé is the first impression that you will have on a re
 cruiter. It must follow these guidelines: \n\n* Professional appearance\n
 \n* MUST utilize an [approved College of Business format] (https://uofnebr
 aska.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/Eny90BK0849Ap_3EPClwQ1I
 B83cvffdDKNQPK0RjUUiy_g?e=YDooCf)\n\n* No text boxes\, tables\, or columns
  are used\n\n* 1 page only\n\n* Consistency between résumé sections evid
 ent\n\n* Required contact information is included (name\, city/state and z
 ip code\, phone number\, email)\n\n* Required information included in the 
 education section (university name\, location\, degree\, major\, graduatio
 n date)\n\n* Required information included in the experience and additiona
 l sections (organization name\, location\, your role\, dates of involvemen
 t)\n\n* Experiences are listed in reverse chronological order\n\n* Referen
 ces are not included or referenced on the document\n\nNote: you are encour
 aged to review the [Revised Résumé assignment] (https://canvas.unl.edu/c
 ourses/208826/assignments/2251666?module_item_id=6205706) again for detail
 ed information and examples of what each section of your résumé should e
 ntail.\n\nStep 3 - Utilize Strong Action Verbs\n--------------------------
 ----------\n\nAction verbs are often one of the first things employers not
 ice when scanning your résumé. Your bullet statements must have:\n\n* De
 scriptions starting with strong action verbs (do not use words like helped
 \, worked\, or assisted)\n\n* Verb tenses which align with the dates of yo
 ur experiences (past experiences should be listed in past tense\; present 
 experiences should be listed in present tense)\n\n* Action verbs that comm
 unicate transferable skills sought after by employers\n\n* Optional: Tail
 or your action verbs by researching action verbs relevant to a specific in
 dustry or job function\n\nStep 4 - Apply the Bullet Statement Formula\n---
 ----------------------------------------\n\nBullet statements must:\n\n* B
 e written utilizing bullet symbols (not written in paragraph format)\n\n* 
 Address only one task per bullet statement\n\n* Be detailed enough to full
 y understand what was done in each role\n\n* Answer\, at minimum\, 2 out o
 f 3 of the components of the what-how-why formula\n\n* What you did in eac
 h role (starting with a strong action verb)\n\n* How you did it well (inco
 rporating skills or the process used)\n\n* Why it mattered (explaining the
  purpose\, result\, or impact)\n\nStep 5 - Incorporate Skills\n-----------
 ----------------\n\nBullet statements are your opportunity to "prove" that
  you can effectively leverage certain skill sets. You must:\n\n* Include r
 eference to transferable skills in your bullet statements\n\n* Do not inc
 lude transferable skills in your skills section\n\n* Optional: Tailor you
 r bullet statements by including reference to both transferable and techni
 cal skills relevant to a particular industry or job function\n\nStep 6 - A
 dd Quantification\n---------------------------\n\nProviding numbers or res
 ults in your bullet statements adds credibility to your experiences. You m
 ust:\n\n* Quantify some experiences throughout your résumé\n\n* While wr
 iting your bullet statements\, ask yourself questions like how many\, how 
 much\, or how often\n\nStep 7 - Review for Spelling & Grammar\n-----------
 ---------------------------\n\nBefore submitting\, ensure that you are usi
 ng strong written communication skills by demonstrating:\n\n* Carefully ch
 osen and conscious writing\n\n* No personal pronouns  (i.e.\, "I"\, "me"\
 , "my"\, "our"\, "we")\n\n* Correct grammar\n\n* Minimal editing mistakes\
 n\n* Evidence of very close proofreading\n\nStep 8 - Make Revisions\n-----
 ------------------\n\nA résumé is an ever-evolving document. After your 
 1:1 coaching session\, you must: \n\n* Make revisions based on your moder
 ator's feedback\n\n* Apply the concepts discussed in your coaching session
 s to improve other components of your document that you were not able to s
 pecifically address\n\nStep 9 - Academic Integrity\n----------------------
 -----\n\nFor this assignment\, it is required to not use external sources\
 , such as a friend's résumé or online template to create your content. Y
 our résumé must be a reflection of your own past experiences and you mus
 t craft your own bullet statements based on those experiences. In short\, 
 you must utilize original thought to communicate your skills and experienc
 e to employers. Plagiarism on the résumé assignment may lead to receivin
 g a final grade of "No Pass." The full version of this policy is in the sy
 llabus.\n\n  Grading and Feedback\n----------------------\n\nGrading: \n
 You will be graded on the following scale:\n\n* Ready: Your résumé is in
  great shape! It has strong bullet statements\, great formatting\, and is 
 free of errors. There may be a few suggested tweaks to make you an even mo
 re competitive applicant\, but you should feel confident utilizing this do
 cument moving forward.\n\n* Almost Ready: Your résumé meets expectations
 \, but there are updates or more strategies you could implement to stand o
 ut. You will not have to resubmit\, but we strongly encourage you to make 
 changes before applying for anything.\n\n* Not Ready: Your résumé did no
 t meet expectations in one or more categories and you have some more work 
 to do. You are required to edit your résumé and resubmit within the time
 line your moderator provides.\n\nModerator Feedback: \nYour moderator wil
 l review your submission and provide suggestions on how to further improve
  your résumé for the future. You must review this feedback and make any 
 necessary changes prior to taking BSAD 333.\n\n  FAQs\n------\n\nHelp! Bu
 llet statement writing is hard. What else can I do? \nIt is. You have to 
 utilize your writing skills in a different way than you are used to. If yo
 u are still struggling after your 1:1 coaching session\, feel free to set 
 up another appointment with your moderator or any other coach in the Busin
 ess Career Center. You can also utilize our drop-in hours (Monday - Friday
  from 1:00-4:00pm). 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Professional Résumé [BSAD-222-951.1261]
