 6&month=04&year=2026#assignment_2251660
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://instructu
 re-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_65070000000000001/attachments/21770615
 /dp_app.css"><div id="dp-wrapper" class="dp-wrapper dp-basic-bar variation
 -2">\n<header class="dp-header dp-basic-bar variation-2 ">\n<h2 class="dp-
 heading"><span class="dp-header-title">Professional Résumé</span></h2>\n
 </header>\n<div class="dp-content-block kl_custom_block_0">\n<h3 class="dp
 -has-icon">\n<i class="fas fa-sync" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dp-ico
 n-content" style="display: none\;">&nbsp\;</span></i> Overview</h3>\n<p><s
 pan>Your résumé is a foundational part of searching for internships and 
 jobs. To be a competitive applicant for positions\, it is critical for you
  to be able to effectively describe your past experiences through your bul
 let statements. </span><strong>This assignment is designed for you to:</st
 rong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Showcase you know how to effectively communicate your
  skills through bullet statement writing</li>\n<li>Receive individualized 
 feedback on your document from a trained career coach</li>\n<li>Ensure you
 r <span>résumé is ready to be utilized for scholarships\, part-time jobs
 \, and internship applications</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Submission
  Requirements:&nbsp\;</strong></p>\n<p><span>Revise your résumé based on
  your moderator's feedback and the instructions and rubric below. It is re
 quired that you make additional edits after your coaching session as we ca
 nnot address every bullet statement during your 45-minute meeting. These e
 dits should include all revisions that your coach mentioned as well as app
 lying the information you learned to bullet statements that you and your m
 oderator did not have a chance to specifically address. Submit the updated
  version of your résumé to Canvas.</span></p>\n<div class=" dp-callout-c
 olor-lt-danger dp-callout card dp-callout-position-default dp-callout-type
 -solid" style="text-align: center\;">\n<div class="card-body">\n<p class="
 card-text"><i class="fas fa-traffic-light card-text" style="color: #000000
 \;" aria-hidden="true"><span style="display: none\;">&nbsp\;</span></i> <s
 pan class="card-text" style="color: #000000\;">&nbsp\;</span><strong class
 ="card-text" style="color: #000000\;">STOP!!! Have you carefully reviewed 
 the rubric and made updates to your </strong><span class="card-text" style
 ="color: #000000\;"><strong>résumé</strong></span><strong class="card-te
 xt" style="color: #000000\;"> based on feedback received in your coaching 
 session?</strong><span class="card-text" style="color: #000000\;"> <br><sp
 an style="font-size: 10pt\;"><em>Remember that you must score at least an 
 "Almost Ready" in EVERY category of the rubric or you will be required to 
 revise and resubmit. Save yourself time and make changes&nbsp\;<span style
 ="text-decoration: underline\;">now</span>.</em></span></span></p>\n</div>
 \n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-content-block kl_custom_block_1">\n<h3 cl
 ass="dp-has-icon">\n<i class="fas fa-book" aria-hidden="true"><span class=
 "dp-icon-content" style="display: none\;">&nbsp\;</span></i> Resources</h3
 >\n<p><strong>This assignment aligns with the <a title="Craft Your Résum
 é Videos" href="https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pages/craft-your-re
 sume-videos-2-2-2" data-course-type="wikiPages" data-published="true" data
 -api-endpoint="https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/courses/208826/pages/craft-yo
 ur-resume-videos-2-2-2" data-api-returntype="Page">Craft Your R</a><span><
 a title="Craft Your Résumé Videos" href="https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/
 208826/pages/craft-your-resume-videos-2-2-2" data-course-type="wikiPages" 
 data-published="true" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/cou
 rses/208826/pages/craft-your-resume-videos-2-2-2" data-api-returntype="Pag
 e">ésumé videos</a> and the <a title="Module 5: Target Your Brand" href=
 "https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/modules/701599" data-api-endpoint="
 https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/courses/208826/modules/701599" data-api-retu
 rntype="Module">Target Your Brand module</a></span></strong>. <span>If you
  have not reviewed this content\, go back before you begin. Other resource
 s that may also be useful include:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class="inline_
 disabled" href="https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/UNL-BusinessCaree
 rCenter/ERkDtkVSzUNGoZaQZx4mi-cBtzmbbXp4v9_6NytjxIY_jg?e=eigR5w" target="_
 blank"><strong>How to Write Bullet Statements</strong></a></li>\n<li><a cl
 ass="inline_disabled" href="https://uofnebraska.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/UNL-B
 usinessCareerCenter/EQ7BbpCIj5ZPt994NDvpJIkBjyNtjtlzz29YT2jQAeGoNw?e=2Xlpj
 D" target="_blank"><strong>Bullet Statement Development Worksheet</strong>
 </a></li>\n<li>\n<strong><a class="inline_disabled" href="https://uofnebra
 ska.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/Eur2cao1mltFsekKNMSHuA0B
 zaH7ewSziXfj9b4F9jjJxA?e=Whjku8" target="_blank"> Industry Specific Keywor
 d Resources</a>&nbsp\; </strong>-&nbsp\;<em>incorporate action verbs and k
 eywords geared toward a specific industry</em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div
  class="dp-content-block kl_custom_block_2">\n<h3 class="dp-has-icon">\n<i
  class="fas fa-clipboard-list" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dp-icon-con
 tent" style="display: none\;">&nbsp\;</span></i> Instructions</h3>\n</div>
 \n<div class="dp-content-block kl_panel_block_0">\n<div class="dp-panels-w
 rapper dp-expander-default">\n<div class="dp-panel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-
 panel-heading active" style="background-color: #d00000 !important\; color:
  #ffffff !important\;">Step 1 - Review Tailoring Options</h3>\n<div class=
 "dp-panel-content active">\n<p><strong>As you apply for future positions\,
  it is important to remember that a <span>résumé is never finished and t
 hat you should tailor your document for each individual role. To help you 
 get started on this\, you have two options when creating your Professional
  Résumé.&nbsp\;</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Option 1:</stro
 ng> Create a universal <span>résumé which you can edit further in the fu
 ture. If you are uncertain of your career plans\, you can write a general 
 résumé to showcase your experiences by communicating commonly sought aft
 er transferable skills (verbal and written communication\, teamwork\, prob
 lem solving\, leadership\, etc.).</span>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Option 2:&n
 bsp\;</strong>Tailor your <span>résumé toward a specific industry\, job 
 function\, or position. This is a great option if you know what type of ca
 reer you want to pursue in the future or are actively applying for positio
 ns. Incorporate keywords based on the industry or job function which you a
 re interested in.</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-pan
 el-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="background-color: #
 d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 2 - Résumé Formatt
 ing and Appearance</h3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\n<p><strong
 >The overall appearance of your<span>&nbsp\;</span> <span>résumé is the 
 first impression that you will have on a recruiter. It must follow these g
 uidelines:&nbsp\;</span> </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<span>Professional app
 earance</span>\n<ul>\n<li><span> <span style="background-color: #fbeeb8\;"
 ><strong>MUST utilize an <a class="inline_disabled" href="https://uofnebra
 ska.sharepoint.com/:f:/s/UNL-BusinessCareerCenter/Eny90BK0849Ap_3EPClwQ1IB
 83cvffdDKNQPK0RjUUiy_g?e=YDooCf" target="_blank">approved College of Busin
 ess format</a></strong></span><br></span></li>\n<li>No text boxes\, tables
 \, or columns are used</li>\n<li><span>1 page only</span></li>\n</ul>\n</l
 i>\n<li>Consistency between résumé sections evident</li>\n<li>Required c
 ontact information is included (name\, city/state and zip code\, phone num
 ber\, email)</li>\n<li>Required information included in the education sect
 ion (university name\, location\, degree\, major\, graduation date)</li>\n
 <li>Required information included in the experience and additional section
 s (organization name\, location\, your role\, dates of involvement)</li>\n
 <li>Experiences are listed in reverse chronological order</li>\n<li>Refere
 nces are not included or referenced on the document</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>No
 te: you are encouraged to review the <a title="Revised Résumé" href="htt
 ps://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/assignments/2251666?module_item_id=6205
 706" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.unl.edu/api/v1/courses/207689/assig
 nments/2158797" data-api-returntype="Assignment"><strong>Revised Résumé 
 assignment</strong></a> again for detailed information and examples of wha
 t each section of your résumé should entail.</em></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<
 div class="dp-panel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="ba
 ckground-color: #d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 3 -
  Utilize Strong Action Verbs</h3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\n
 <p><strong>Action verbs are often one of the first things employers notice
  when scanning your résumé. Your bullet statements must have:</strong></
 p>\n<ul>\n<li>Descriptions starting with strong action verbs (<strong><spa
 n style="text-decoration: underline\;">do not use</span> </strong>words li
 ke helped\, worked\, or assisted)</li>\n<li>Verb tenses which align with t
 he dates of your experiences (past experiences should be listed in past te
 nse\; present experiences should be listed in present tense)</li>\n<li>Act
 ion verbs that communicate transferable skills sought after by employers</
 li>\n<li>\n<em>Optional:&nbsp\;</em>Tailor your action verbs by researchin
 g action verbs relevant to a specific industry or job function</li>\n</ul>
 \n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-panel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-headin
 g active" style="background-color: #d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !im
 portant\;">Step 4 - Apply the Bullet Statement Formula</h3>\n<div class="d
 p-panel-content active">\n<p><strong>Bullet statements must:</strong></p>\
 n<ul>\n<li>Be written utilizing bullet symbols (<span style="text-decorati
 on: underline\;"><strong>not </strong></span>written in paragraph format)<
 /li>\n<li>Address only one task per bullet statement</li>\n<li>Be detailed
  enough to fully understand what was done in each role</li>\n<li>Answer\, 
 at minimum\, 2 out of 3 of the components of the what-how-why formula\n<ul
 >\n<li><em>What you did in each role (starting with a strong action verb)<
 /em></li>\n<li><em>How you did it well (incorporating skills or the proces
 s used)</em></li>\n<li><em>Why it mattered (explaining the purpose\, resul
 t\, or impact)</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=
 "dp-panel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="background-c
 olor: #d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 5 - Incorpora
 te Skills</h3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\n<p><strong>Bullet s
 tatements are your opportunity to "prove" that you can effectively leverag
 e certain skill sets. You must:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Include reference 
 to transferable skills in your bullet statements</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Do no
 t&nbsp\;</strong>include transferable skills in your skills section</li>\n
 <li>\n<em>Optional:&nbsp\;</em>Tailor your bullet statements by including 
 reference to both transferable and technical skills relevant to a particul
 ar industry or job function</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-pa
 nel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="background-color: 
 #d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 6 - Add Quantificat
 ion</h3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\n<p><strong>Providing numb
 ers or results in your bullet statements adds credibility to your experien
 ces. You must:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Quantify some experiences throughou
 t your résumé\n<ul>\n<li><em>While writing your bullet statements\, ask 
 yourself questions like <strong>how many\, how much\, </strong>or<strong> 
 how often</strong></em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div cl
 ass="dp-panel-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="backgrou
 nd-color: #d00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 7 - Revie
 w for Spelling &amp\; Grammar</h3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\
 n<p><strong>Before submitting\, ensure that you are using strong written c
 ommunication skills by demonstrating:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Carefully ch
 osen and conscious writing</li>\n<li>\n<strong>No personal pronouns&nbsp\;
 </strong> <span>(i.e.\, "I"\, "me"\, "my"\, "our"\, "we")</span>\n</li>\n<
 li>Correct grammar</li>\n<li>Minimal editing mistakes</li>\n<li>Evidence o
 f very close proofreading</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-pane
 l-group">\n<h3 class="dp-panel-heading active" style="background-color: #d
 00000 !important\; color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 8 - Make Revisions</h
 3>\n<div class="dp-panel-content active">\n<p><strong>A résumé is an eve
 r-evolving document. After your 1:1 coaching session\, you must:&nbsp\;</s
 trong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make revisions based on your moderator's feedback</l
 i>\n<li>Apply the concepts discussed in your coaching sessions to improve 
 other components of your document that you were not able to specifically a
 ddress</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-panel-group">\n<h3 clas
 s="dp-panel-heading active" style="background-color: #d00000 !important\; 
 color: #ffffff !important\;">Step 9 - Academic Integrity</h3>\n<div class=
 "dp-panel-content active">\n<p>For this assignment\, it is required to not
  use external sources\, such as a friend's<strong> </strong>résumé or on
 line template to create your content. Your résumé must be a reflection o
 f your own past experiences and you must craft your own bullet statements 
 based on those experiences. In short\, y<span>ou must utilize original tho
 ught to communicate your skills and experience to employers. Plagiarism on
  the résumé assignment may lead to receiving a final grade of "No Pass."
  </span><em>The full version of this policy is in the syllabus.</em></p>\n
 </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-content-block kl_custom_blo
 ck_3">\n<h3 class="dp-has-icon">\n<i class="fas fa-share-square" aria-hidd
 en="true"><span class="dp-icon-content" style="display: none\;">&nbsp\;</s
 pan></i> Grading and Feedback</h3>\n<p><strong>Grading:&nbsp\;</strong> <b
 r>You will be graded on the following scale:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Read
 y:</strong> Your <span>résumé is in great shape! It has strong bullet st
 atements\, great formatting\, and is free of errors. There may be a few su
 ggested tweaks to make you an even more competitive applicant\, but you sh
 ould feel confident utilizing this document moving forward.</span>\n</li>\
 n<li>\n<strong>Almost Ready:</strong> <span>Your résumé meets expectatio
 ns\, but there are updates or more strategies you could implement to stand
  out. You will not have to resubmit\, but we strongly encourage you to mak
 e changes before applying for anything.</span>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Not R
 eady:</strong> Your <span>résumé did not meet expectations in <span styl
 e="text-decoration: underline\;">one or more categories</span> and you hav
 e some more work to do. <span style="background-color: #fbeeb8\;"><strong>
 You are required to edit your résumé and resubmit within the timeline yo
 ur moderator provides.</strong></span> </span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>M
 oderator Feedback:&nbsp\;</strong> <br>Your moderator will review your sub
 mission and provide suggestions on how to further improve your <span>résu
 mé for the future. You must review this feedback and make any necessary c
 hanges prior to taking BSAD 333.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class="dp-conten
 t-block kl_custom_block_4">\n<h3 class="dp-has-icon">\n<i class="far fa-qu
 estion-circle" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dp-icon-content" style="dis
 play: none\;">&nbsp\;</span></i> FAQs</h3>\n<p><strong>Help! Bullet statem
 ent writing is hard. What else can I do?&nbsp\;</strong> <br>It is. You ha
 ve to utilize your writing skills in a different way than you are used to.
  If you are still struggling after your 1:1 coaching session\, feel free t
 o set up another appointment with your moderator or any other coach in the
  Business Career Center. You can also utilize our drop-in hours (Monday - 
 Friday from 1:00-4:00pm).&nbsp\;</p>\n</div>\n</div><script src="https://i
 nstructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_65070000000000001/attachments/
 21770614/dp_app.js"></script>
END:VEVENT
