DESCRIPTION:An informational interview is a conversation that provides you
  an opportunity to seek insight into a career path\, industry\, or organiz
 ation from a professional currently in the field. Please reflect on your i
 nformational interview experience in this assignment\, highlighting what y
 ou learned about the person\, their work\, and how it does and doesn't ali
 gn with your own strengths and goals.\n\nSee the "[Informational Interview
  Assignment Outline & Resources] (https://canvas.unl.edu/courses/208826/pa
 ges/informational-interview-assignment-outline-and-resources-2-2)" for gui
 dance\, a list of FAQs\, and more details on the assignment's learning obj
 ectives and expectations.\n\nGrading:\nThis is a complete/incomplete assig
 nment. You will receive a complete if your reflection has all the required
  information and includes an in-depth reflection of your experience.\n\nNo
 te: If you score lower than the full 35 points\, you are required to revie
 w your moderator's feedback and resubmit within the timeline provided.
